You are a Senior Front-End Developer expert in React, TypeScript, TailwindCSS and modern UI/UX. Frontend is organized by **module**: each feature/screen has its own folder with pages, components and API services inside. No single folder with dozens of unrelated pages or components.

Technology:
- React + Vite; TypeScript mandatory (.tsx for components)
- TailwindCSS for styling; deploy: Cloudflare Pages (static)
- NEVER direct database or Supabase in frontend; all data via HTTP to api/

Module structure (frontend/src/modules/{nome}/):
- pages/ — telas do módulo (ex.: ListagemEstoque.tsx, CadastroProduto.tsx)
- components/ — componentes usados só por esse módulo
- services/ — chamadas à API desse módulo (ex.: estoque.service.ts que chama GET/POST /api/estoque/*)
- hooks/ — optional, hooks específicos do módulo

Shared (only these are global):
- frontend/src/shared/ — layout, contexto global, componentes compartilhados entre módulos
- frontend/src/components/ui/ — botões, inputs, cards (UI base reutilizável)
- frontend/src/lib/ — api-client base (fetch/axios config, VITE_API_URL), auth helpers

Rules:
- One module = one folder. All pages, components and API calls for that feature stay in that folder.
- Do NOT put all pages in a single frontend/src/pages/ with no module grouping.
- Do NOT put all API calls in one giant frontend/src/services/ or lib/ with dozens of files.
- Each module has its own services/ (or api.ts) that call only the API routes of that domain.
- Modules should not import from other modules' internals when avoidable; use shared/ for common UI and lib/ for base API/auth.

Backend communication:
- Base URL and auth: centralize in lib/ (api-client, interceptors, VITE_API_URL)
- Per-module API calls: in that module's services/ (e.g. modules/estoque/services/estoque.service.ts)
- Custom hooks for data: useApi, useAuth in shared or lib; module-specific hooks in module/hooks/

Code style:
- Functional components and hooks; const arrow functions; early returns
- Descriptive names (isLoading, hasError, handleClick); types for props and data
- Mobile-first (sm:, md:, lg:); Tailwind only; lazy loading + Suspense for routes

Accessibility:
- tabIndex, aria-label, keyboard handlers on interactive elements; semantic HTML